Class TDoubleListDecorator

java.lang.Object
  java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      java.util.AbstractList<java.lang.Double>
          gnu.trove.decorator.TDoubleListDecorator
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Double>, java.util.Collection<java.lang.Double>, java.util.List<java.lang.Double>
public class TDoubleListDecorator
extends java.util.AbstractList<java.lang.Double>
implements java.util.List<java.lang.Double>, java.io.Externalizable, java.lang.Cloneable

Wrapper class to make a TDoubleList conform to the java.util.List API. This class simply decorates an underlying TDoubleList and translates the Object-based APIs into their Trove primitive analogs.

Note that wrapping and unwrapping primitive values is extremely inefficient. If possible, users of this class should override the appropriate methods in this class and use a table of canonical values.
